## 🐧 Step 1: Install Ubuntu

Install Ubuntu using one of the following methods:

From Microsoft Store (recommended for Windows users)
            Or 
Download from: https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop

## ⚙️ Step 2: Update System Packages

>sudo apt update

## 🐍 Step 3: Install Python & Virtual Environment

>sudo apt install python3-venv python3-full -y

Explanation:
* **python3-venv** → Used to create virtual environments
* **python3-full** → Provides complete Python support

## 🧱 Step 4: Create Virtual Environment

# Create virtual environment
>python3 -m venv airflow_env

# Activate it
>source airflow_env/bin/activate

You should see:
(airflow_env)

5. Set Airflow Home
>export AIRFLOW_HOME=~/airflow
Airflow will store everything here:
~/airflow/
 ├── dags/
 ├── logs/
 ├── airflow.db

6. Install Airflow
>pip install "apache-airflow==2.9.0" \
--constraint "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/apache/airflow/constraints-2.9.0/constraints-3.10.txt"

7. Initialize Database
>airflow db init

8. Create Admin User
>airflow users create \
--username admin \
--firstname Harini \
--lastname K \
--role Admin \
--email admin@example.com \
--password admin

8. Start Airflow
Terminal 1:
>airflow webserver --port 8080

Terminal 2:
>airflow scheduler

```
http://localhost:8080-- open in browser to see airflow Dashboard
```

Note: Each and Every time if you add any dag fn you need to restart the scheduler, if not the dag will not be reflected in UI. 
